        "mode": "full",
        "content": "# TSLA \u2014 Technicals\n\n## TL;DR\n\nTSLA was in a confirmed daily downtrend across all three runs in April 2026. ADX hit 29.5 on April 11 with EMAs aligned bearish. The stock oscillated from a low near $347 up to $392 during a bear rally into earnings, then returned to hold territory post-earnings. No run produced a clean long setup; the April 15 short at $391.86 was the only actionable trade taken, and it was minimal-sized due to earnings risk.\n\n## Multi-timeframe state\n\n| Timeframe | State | Source run |\n|---|---|---|\n| Daily | Downtrend confirmed; EMAs bearish-aligned; ADX 29.5 | swing_20260411_211655 |\n| Daily | Downtrend intact; supertrend bearish; momentum 5d+ vs 21d- divergence | 20260417_233350 |\n| Hourly | Uptrend (counter to daily) on Apr 17 \u2014 creating directional conflict | 20260417_233350 |\n| Hourly | Fib/EMA resistance cluster 387\u2013399 on Apr 15 | 20260415_093758 |\n\nThe April 17 run explicitly called out \"daily downtrend vs hourly uptrend conflict; momentum divergence 5d+ vs 21d-\" as the reason for a hold decision. Multi-timeframe disagreement is a red flag for swing setups.\n\n## Key levels\n\n| Level | Value | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Major resistance | $399\u2013$408 | Stop-loss zone Apr 15 run; hourly EMA cluster |\n| Bear-rally resistance | $387\u2013$399 | Fib/EMA confluence; entry reference Apr 15 |\n| 10 EMA | ~$357 | Apr 11 bounce target reference |\n| Price floor (Apr run) | $343\u2013$349 | Apr 11 target price; Apr 15 short target $343.80 |\n| JPMorgan bear target | $145 | Extreme bear case; not a near-term level |\n\n## Setup type\n\n**Bear-rally short** \u2014 the only setup the model executed. Rationale on April 15: \"Daily downtrend confirmed; bear rally into EMA/Fib resistance cluster $387\u2013$399; 4 bearish strategies.\" The 6.21:1 risk-reward (entry $391.86, target $343.80, stop $399.60) was attractive but confidence was only 49% due to the April 22 earnings binary.\n\nOn April 11, the model wanted to short but the R:R was only 1.5:1 (19pt target vs 13pt stop), which failed the 2:1 minimum. It called for waiting for a bounce to $357 (10 EMA) for a better entry.\n\nOn April 17, the multi-timeframe conflict (daily bear vs hourly bull) and R:R of 1.64 put TSLA back on hold.\n\n## Last updated\n\n2026-04-29. Prices are as of the respective run dates (April 11, 15, 17). Levels will be stale within 7 days \u2014 refresh from next swing run signals.\n",
        "last_updated": "2026-04-29",
        "stale": false
